<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11008b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11008b">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11008b"> 8(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> scurrilous</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Ballinasloe Mental Hospital.</b> &hellip; A letter from the Sinn Fein executive, East Galway, saying that a report has recently appeared in the public Press concerning the treatment meted out to an attendant in the institution. &ldquo;The man evidently was refused reinstatement by your officials, the letter stated, for the sole reason that he was a Republican. We thought the days of Orange bigotry were over, even in the asylum. &hellip;&mdash;M. Connolly, hon. Sec.&rdquo; / Dr. Mills said he thought the letter was an attack on him. &hellip; Fr. Dunne: Mark the letter &ldquo;read.&rdquo;&mdash;Mr. Curley: It is a <mark>scurrilous</mark> letter.&mdash;Fr. Dunne: Indeed, it is not a nice production.&mdash;The letter was marked &ldquo;read.&rdquo; <small> <a name="CT17may24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CT17may24"><cite title="source">Connacht Tribune</cite></a> (17 May 1924) 3/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
